<p><b>Why is German grammar so complex?</b> German grammar is notorious for its complexity, and it's not hard to see why: Cases Galore: German has four cases (nominative, accusative, dative, genitive) that affect nouns, pronouns, and articles. This means you have to juggle different endings based on the role of a word in a sentence.</p>
