<p><b>How long does it take to learn German grammar?</b> The Foreign Service Institute (FSI) estimates that learning German will take about 30 weeks, or 750 classroom hours, as it is rated as a category two language similar to English.</p>
<p><b>In what order should you learn German grammar?</b> Generally, it's recommended that you start with the accusative case. Then, once you know that, you can move on to dative. Finally, you can learn the genitive case last. This order makes the most sense within the broader context of German grammar.</p>